Java concurrency question: why is this final count sometimes wrong, and what's the simplest thread-safe fix? Please explain briefly and show the corrected code for inc().

Code:
import java.util.*;

public class Demo {
    static class Counter {
        int count = 0;
        void inc() {
            count++; // expected 100_000 after all threads finish
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        Counter c = new Counter();
        List<Thread> threads = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
            Thread t = new Thread(() -> {
                for (int j = 0; j < 1000; j++) c.inc();
            });
            threads.add(t);
            t.start();
        }
        for (Thread t : threads) t.join();
        System.out.println(c.count);
    }
}

